2.00	Pierre_plantard	Pierre Plantard	Pierre Athanase Marie Plantard (18 March 1920 â€“ 3 February 2000) was a French draughtsman, best known for being the principal perpetrator of the Priory of Sion hoax, by which he claimed from the 1960s onwards that he was a Merovingian descendant of Dagobert II and the "Great Monarch" prophesied by Nostradamus. Today in France he is commonly regarded as a mystificator.	
